If a Rackspace Cloud account requires multi-factor authentication, users who have not set up
      and enabled multi-factor authentication get the following response when they authenticate:
      HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden
       Vary:  Accept, Accept-Encoding, X-Auth-Token
       Content-Type: application/json
      {
        "forbidden": {
        "code": 403,
        "message": "User must setup multi-factor"
         }
      }

